!!Use at your own risk!!

ADS-B Aircraft Tracking

Ubuntu 24.04.4
Docker 29.3.1
RTL-SDR v3

Install Dependencies
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y git cmake libusb-1.0-0-dev pkg-config

Blacklist the default TV drivers
echo 'blacklist rtl2832' | sudo tee /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist-rtl.conf
echo 'blacklist rtl2832_sdr' | sudo tee -a /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist-rtl.conf
echo 'blacklist dvb_usb_rtl28xxu' | sudo tee -a /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist-rtl.conf
sudo modprobe -r dvb_usb_rtl28xxu

If last command returns busy either reboot or do cleanup with rmmod
sudo lsmod | egrep rtl
rtl2832_sdr            45056  0
videobuf2_vmalloc      20480  1 rtl2832_sdr
videobuf2_v4l2         36864  1 rtl2832_sdr
videobuf2_common       81920  4 rtl2832_sdr,videobuf2_vmalloc,videobuf2_v4l2,videobuf2_memops
rtl2832                32768  1
i2c_mux                12288  1 rtl2832
dvb_usb_rtl28xxu       45056  1
dvb_usb_v2             53248  1 dvb_usb_rtl28xxu
rc_core                73728  4 dvb_usb_v2,dvb_usb_rtl28xxu,cec
videodev              352256  5 v4l2_async,rtl2832_sdr,v4l2_fwnode,videobuf2_v4l2,ov13858

Install dump1090-fa (FlightAware version):
docker run --rm -d \
    --device /dev/bus/usb \
    --restart unless-stopped \
    --name dump1090 \
    -p 8080:8080 \
    jraviles/dump1090:latest

docker logs dump1090
Wed Jun 17 23:38:21 2026 UTC  dump1090-fa unknown starting up.
rtlsdr: using device #0: Generic RTL2832U OEM (Realtek, RTL2838UHIDIR, SN 00000001)
Found Rafael Micro R820T tuner
rtlsdr: tuner gain set to 49.6 dB (gain step 28)

Access the Local Data Feed
http://localhost:8080
If you see a map with planes, your hardware and software are working correctly!

curl -s http://localhost:8080/data/aircraft.json | head -c 200
